timeline.bodyText:
we can't remove functions as that would introduce backward compatibility issues in our java client. So we should also have a function with the original arguments:
public Roles getRoles(String domainName, Boolean members) { return getRoles(domainName, members, null, null); }
For the Go client we don't have a wrapper so no option but to update your client code as necessary, but for java we have the wrapper thus we always maintain backward compatibility

